00:29:15,255 --> 00:29:17,215
I was sent down here
for an engine room punch.

459
00:29:17,216 --> 00:29:18,758
- XO send you?
- Yes, Chief.

460
00:29:18,759 --> 00:29:21,427
Yeah?
Look at that nose.

461
00:29:21,428 --> 00:29:23,908
Look at that nose!
Look at it.

462
00:29:26,558 --> 00:29:28,809
You can be thankful
you didn't get an engine room punch

463
00:29:28,810 --> 00:29:30,520
- in the nose.
- Y-yes, Chief.

464
00:29:30,521 --> 00:29:32,855
I wouldn't worry
about it, though.

465
00:29:32,856 --> 00:29:35,107
Our luck will hold

466
00:29:35,108 --> 00:29:36,651
as long as we have
our little white dove of peace here.

467
00:29:36,652 --> 00:29:39,403
She's our good luck charm.
All right, back to work!

468
00:29:39,404 --> 00:29:41,280
Captain wants the boat
at top speed.

469
00:29:41,281 --> 00:29:43,407
Chief, doves have longer
tail feathers.

470
00:29:43,408 --> 00:29:45,159
That's a pigeon.

471
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:47,180
I know. my father
raises pigeons.

472
00:29:53,377 --> 00:29:54,847
Hmm.

473
00:29:57,714 --> 00:29:59,549
<i><font color="#D09090">CHARLIE</font> :
We accomplished our mission,</i>

474
00:29:59,550 --> 00:30:04,490
<i>reaching Tinian in record time
with zero casualties.</i>

475
00:30:17,776 --> 00:30:20,444
<i>I fear the cargo
we were dropping off</i>

476
00:30:20,445 --> 00:30:23,656
<i>could change
the nature of war forever.</i>

477
00:30:23,657 --> 00:30:27,368
<i>Our next assignment
would be to return to combat,</i>

478
00:30:27,369 --> 00:30:30,830
<i>but we were still
being denied our escort</i>

479
00:30:30,831 --> 00:30:33,981
<b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b>

