00:31:31,266 --> 00:31:33,684
<font color="#D900D9">(COUGHS)</font>

481
00:31:33,685 --> 00:31:35,561
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)</font>

482
00:31:35,562 --> 00:31:38,564
To the best chaplain
we ever had!

483
00:31:38,565 --> 00:31:40,900
<font color="#D09090">ALL</font> : <b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b> For he's
a jolly good fellow <b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b>

484
00:31:40,901 --> 00:31:43,402
<b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b> For he's
a jolly good fellow <b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b>

485
00:31:43,403 --> 00:31:47,323
<b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b> For he's a
jolly good fellow <b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b>

486
00:31:47,324 --> 00:31:50,284
<b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b> Which nobody can deny. <b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b>

487
00:31:50,285 --> 00:31:52,703
<font color="#D900D9">(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)</font>

488
00:31:52,704 --> 00:31:54,539
Congrats on
your last tour, chaps.

489
00:31:54,540 --> 00:31:55,998
Thanks, boys.

490
00:31:55,999 --> 00:31:58,292
I think I'm gonna take this one back
in my quarters.

491
00:31:58,293 --> 00:31:59,919
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL GROANING)</font>

492
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:02,380
Come on, short timer,
stay with us.

493
00:32:02,381 --> 00:32:04,048
I do appreciate Deuce
for not sneaking

494
00:32:04,049 --> 00:32:06,592
any unclothed women
in here tonight.

495
00:32:06,593 --> 00:32:09,303
Listen up, Standish
is on the prowl, all right?

496
00:32:09,304 --> 00:32:10,471
So keep it down.

497
00:32:10,472 --> 00:32:12,431
Alvin, I know
that's tough for you.

498
00:32:12,432 --> 00:32:15,017
Hey, I'm innocent as a dove,
father, you know me.

499
00:32:15,018 --> 00:32:17,538
- <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER)</font>
- Thanks, fellas.

500
00:32:22,276 --> 00:32:26,612
Admiral, I understand that
we are to sail to Leyte.

501
00:32:26,613 --> 00:32:29,574
Now that we have
delivered the packages,

502
00:32:29,575 --> 00:32:32,743
can we please have our escort?

503
00:32:32,744 --> 00:32:35,663
Charlie, how can you
have an escort?

504
00:32:35,664 --> 00:32:37,604
You were never here.

505
00:32:42,754 --> 00:32:44,589
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHANTING)</font>
Go! Go! Go! Go!

506
00:32:44,590 --> 00:32:48,509
Go! Go! Go! Go!
Go! Go! Go! Go! go!

507
00:32:48,510 --> 00:32:50,428
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEER)</font>

508
00:32:50,429 --> 00:32:51,637
Listen up, listen up,

509
00:32:51,638 --> 00:32:54,765
hey, hey,
who am I? Huh? Huh?

510
00:32:54,766 --> 00:32:58,352
- Hey! I'll have y'all know...
- <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER)</font>

511
00:32:58,353 --> 00:33:01,772
That I graduated second in
my class at the Naval Academy!

512
00:33:01,773 --> 00:33:03,858
Whoo!
<font color="#D900D9">(BLOWS RASPBERRY)</font>

513
00:33:03,859 --> 00:33:08,779
And I'm going to turn you into lean,
mean fighting machines!

514
00:33:08,780 --> 00:33:12,366
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER)</font>

515
00:33:12,367 --> 00:33:13,967
Attention on deck!

516
00:33:14,953 --> 00:33:16,143
Signalman!

517
00:33:19,791 --> 00:33:22,084
Where did you get that alcohol?

518
00:33:22,085 --> 00:33:24,504
It's actually mine.

519
00:33:24,505 --> 00:33:26,515
Is that so?

520
00:33:28,592 --> 00:33:31,742
And that liquor on his breath?
Is that yours, too?

521
00:33:35,641 --> 00:33:40,478
Swab up that giggle water.
We're shipping out!

522
00:33:40,479 --> 00:33:44,398
There will be no liberty!
We're received our orders.

523
00:33:44,399 --> 00:33:47,026
And you'll all be on mess hall duty
effective immediately.

524
00:33:47,027 --> 00:33:51,757
This isn't a minstrel show.
This is the United States Navy!

525
00:33:53,534 --> 00:33:56,474
And I graduated first
in my class, by the way.

526
00:33:58,747 --> 00:34:00,427
<font color="#D900D9">(CUP CLANGS)</font>

527
00:34:03,836 --> 00:34:06,016
<font color="#D900D9">(SHIP'S HORN BLOWS)</font>

528
00:34:18,684 --> 00:34:20,893
What in the hell?
That ain't your bag.

529
00:34:20,894 --> 00:34:23,437
No, it's Alvin's.
I think he took the ring.

530
00:34:23,438 --> 00:34:25,648
Hey, you're gonna get busted.

531
00:34:25,649 --> 00:34:28,651
I checked Sanchez and West.

532
00:34:28,652 --> 00:34:30,820
Nothing. Shit.

533
00:34:30,821 --> 00:34:33,906
Hey, thanks for helping me
out the other night with Standish.

534
00:34:33,907 --> 00:34:36,534
Wouldn't want you
to jeopardize your promotion.

535
00:34:36,535 --> 00:34:38,161
All right, look,

536
00:34:38,162 --> 00:34:41,622
the whole reason
that this ship is on a course

537
00:34:41,623 --> 00:34:43,875
is 'cause they charted a plan
and they followed it.

538
00:34:43,876 --> 00:34:46,878
So it's lucky Clara
didn't get a chance to say yes

539
00:34:46,879 --> 00:34:49,589
because I'm incapable
of making a plan,

540
00:34:49,590 --> 00:34:51,174
incapable of supporting her.

541
00:34:51,175 --> 00:34:53,509
I'm just saying maybe things
turned out for the best.

542
00:34:53,510 --> 00:34:56,762
My plan is to find
the son of a bitch that stole my ring

543
00:34:56,763 --> 00:34:59,724
and marry her the second
I get off this ship,

544
00:34:59,725 --> 00:35:01,893
and I don't care
what her parents or you

545
00:35:01,894 --> 00:35:03,603
or anybody else
has got to say...

546
00:35:03,604 --> 00:35:05,771
You the kid
that does the diving?

547
00:35:05,772 --> 00:35:08,441
Oh, you mean the all-knowing
Brian Smithwick?

548
00:35:08,442 --> 00:35:10,712
Yeah, that's him.

549
00:35:12,571 --> 00:35:14,113
Yeah, I do a little diving.

550
00:35:14,114 --> 00:35:16,574
Okay, man, we want
to know about sharks.

551
00:35:16,575 --> 00:35:19,118
I've been telling
Lindy here that sharks

552
00:35:19,119 --> 00:35:21,454
don't really bother you
unless you're bleeding.

553
00:35:21,455 --> 00:35:24,675
If you're bleeding,
it's a problem.

554
00:35:28,962 --> 00:35:31,192
I get nosebleeds.

555
00:35:32,841 --> 00:35:33,841
<i><font color="#D900D9">(BELL RINGS)</font></i>

556
00:35:33,842 --> 00:35:34,992
Captain's on the bridge.

557
00:35:36,803 --> 00:35:39,555
Captain, some of the men
are sleeping on deck again.

558
00:35:39,556 --> 00:35:40,932
Let them.

559
00:35:40,933 --> 00:35:43,100
Their racks
are hotter than Hades.

560
00:35:43,101 --> 00:35:45,561
- Visibility?
- Just this side of poor, sir,

561
00:35:45,562 --> 00:35:47,772
Got a fog rolling in.

562
00:35:47,773 --> 00:35:50,024
Let's get through this weather
as quickly as possible.

563
00:35:50,025 --> 00:35:53,569
Cease zigzagging until the fog clears,
full speed ahead.

564
00:35:53,570 --> 00:35:55,863
- Aye aye.
- Standish.

565
00:35:55,864 --> 00:35:57,114
Full speed ahead.

566
00:35:57,115 --> 00:36:00,535
Full speed ahead, boys.
Full speed ahead.

567
00:36:00,536 --> 00:36:03,204
I hear you put 24 men
on mess hall duty for a week.

568
00:36:03,205 --> 00:36:05,998
Yes, sir, I'm gonna
write them all up as well.

569
00:36:05,999 --> 00:36:08,543
The Japanese are extremely
disciplined adversary, sir.

570
00:36:08,544 --> 00:36:09,961
If we are to defeat them...

571
00:36:09,962 --> 00:36:14,232
Sometimes it's better
to be respected than feared.

572
00:36:33,068 --> 00:36:35,918
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING JAPANESE)</font>

573
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:47,770
<i><font color="#D900D9">(SONAR PINGING)</font></i>

574
00:36:57,718 --> 00:37:00,738
<font color="#D900D9">(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

575
00:37:06,852 --> 00:37:07,894
- D'Antonio.
- What?

576
00:37:07,895 --> 00:37:09,020
Night watch is that way.

577
00:37:09,021 --> 00:37:10,605
- He took the ring.
- What?

578
00:37:10,606 --> 00:37:12,064
<i>The engagement ring,
Deuce took it</i>

579
00:37:12,065 --> 00:37:13,649
when he pulled me
out of the fight,

580
00:37:13,650 --> 00:37:15,651
- pickpocketing son of a bitch.
- Come on, Deuce?

581
00:37:15,652 --> 00:37:17,632
Ugh, you smell like
a distillery.

582
00:37:26,038 --> 00:37:28,915
Might as well go on and admit.
You was scared, boy.

583
00:37:28,916 --> 00:37:32,585
Scared? Of you?
You hit like a girl.

584
00:37:32,586 --> 00:37:36,214
Next time I'm scared of a fight,
it'll be the first damn time.

585
00:37:36,215 --> 00:37:40,259
Boy, you better be glad them MPs
saved your ass from us.

586
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:42,345
Else we have to take you
like this chicken bone here.

587
00:37:42,346 --> 00:37:44,347
Hey, Mr. Big Talk,

588
00:37:44,348 --> 00:37:45,389
whatever you do to that there

589
00:37:45,390 --> 00:37:46,849
flight deck buzzard bone,

590
00:37:46,850 --> 00:37:49,727
that's exactly what
I'm going to do to you

591
00:37:49,728 --> 00:37:53,788
when I get out of his cage
and I catch you alone.

592
00:37:58,946 --> 00:38:02,126
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

593
00:38:05,327 --> 00:38:07,347
<i>You suck that bone
like you've done that before!</i>

594
00:38:11,041 --> 00:38:12,981
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING JAPANESE)</font>

595
00:38:21,718 --> 00:38:23,778
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SHOUTING IN JAPANESE)</font>

596
00:38:37,693 --> 00:38:38,793
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING)</font>

597
00:38:52,457 --> 00:38:56,294
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHATTERING)</font>

598
00:38:56,295 --> 00:38:58,337
Lady Luck is a friend of mine.

599
00:38:58,338 --> 00:39:01,424
Open up
and let it shine. Huh?

600
00:39:01,425 --> 00:39:03,065
Yeah.

601
00:39:04,803 --> 00:39:07,163
- Come on, now,
- Here we go, we go.

602
00:39:09,766 --> 00:39:11,976
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SHOUTING)</font>

603
00:39:11,977 --> 00:39:14,037
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING JAPANESE)</font>

604
00:39:33,415 --> 00:39:34,515
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS JAPANESE)</font>

605
00:39:37,461 --> 00:39:42,006
<i><font color="#D900D9">(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)</font></i>

606
00:39:42,007 --> 00:39:44,842
Ah, yeah, doc.
Okay.

607
00:39:44,843 --> 00:39:46,969
Yeah. Mmm.

608
00:39:46,970 --> 00:39:49,013
Deuce, where's my ring?

609
00:39:49,014 --> 00:39:51,307
- What the hell you talking about?
- Oh, no, you know exactly

610
00:39:51,308 --> 00:39:54,208
- what I'm talking about!
- No, I don't know what you're talking about!

611
00:39:56,313 --> 00:39:58,463
Double or nothing!
Hey!

612
00:40:02,027 --> 00:40:03,997
<i><font color="#D900D9">(EXPLOSIONS)</font></i>

613
00:40:05,405 --> 00:40:06,795
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN</font> :
Oh, my God!</i>

614
00:40:10,077 --> 00:40:12,495
<i><font color="#D900D9">(ALARM BLARING)</font></i>

615
00:40:12,496 --> 00:40:14,056
General quarters!

616
00:40:19,378 --> 00:40:20,848
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKS JAPANESE)</font>

617
00:40:30,264 --> 00:40:31,931
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING)</font>

618
00:40:31,932 --> 00:40:33,872
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTING, CLAMORING)</font>

619
00:40:35,394 --> 00:40:37,964
- Out of the way!
- <font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

620
00:40:44,403 --> 00:40:45,503
<font color="#D900D9">(SIZZLES)</font>

621
00:40:46,572 --> 00:40:48,156
Report!

622
00:40:48,157 --> 00:40:51,033
All comms are down, sir!
I tried to stop the engines!

623
00:40:51,034 --> 00:40:52,910
- But I don't know if the signal went through!
- Stay calm.

624
00:40:52,911 --> 00:40:54,412
Cavanaugh,
keep trying to get through.

625
00:40:54,413 --> 00:40:57,290
Standish, I want eyes
on the damage.

626
00:40:57,291 --> 00:40:59,041
<font color="#D900D9">(MUTTERS)</font>

627
00:40:59,042 --> 00:41:02,562
You heard the captain!
Go! Go!

628
00:41:04,298 --> 00:41:08,050
Fire control, fire control now!
Hoses, starboard side.

629
00:41:08,051 --> 00:41:09,093
Get that fire out!

630
00:41:09,094 --> 00:41:11,914
<i><font color="#D900D9">(EXPLOSIONS)</font></i>

631
00:41:13,015 --> 00:41:15,558
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

632
00:41:15,559 --> 00:41:18,539
Shut the engines down!
Shut them down!

633
00:41:21,899 --> 00:41:23,379
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

634
00:41:32,910 --> 00:41:34,430
<font color="#D900D9">(SHOUTS)</font>

635
00:41:36,288 --> 00:41:40,888
<font color="#D900D9">(CLAMORING, SHOUTING)</font>

636
00:41:45,589 --> 00:41:47,131
Are we getting through?

637
00:41:47,132 --> 00:41:49,842
Radios are down,
but I Jerry-rigged the wires.

638
00:41:49,843 --> 00:41:51,302
- You sent the SOS out?
- Yes sir.

639
00:41:51,303 --> 00:41:52,845
Look at the needles.
They're moving.

640
00:41:52,846 --> 00:41:54,906
Good work. Carry on.

641
00:41:56,600 --> 00:41:58,910
<i><font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMING)</font></i>

642
00:42:01,897 --> 00:42:04,917
<font color="#D900D9">(BOTH SHOUTING)</font>

643
00:42:07,194 --> 00:42:09,070
Don't touch it with your hands!

644
00:42:09,071 --> 00:42:11,322
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

645
00:42:11,323 --> 00:42:13,053
I told you not to touch it!

646
00:42:18,205 --> 00:42:19,956
Come on, come on,
come on, come on!

647
00:42:19,957 --> 00:42:21,624
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMING)</font>

648
00:42:21,625 --> 00:42:23,935
We gotta go.
We gotta go!

649
00:42:27,965 --> 00:42:29,935
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEER)</font>

650
00:42:33,011 --> 00:42:35,638
<i>USS Indianapolis trying to
establish any and all contact.</i>

651
00:42:35,639 --> 00:42:37,598
- Does anybody copy?
- Anything?

652
00:42:37,599 --> 00:42:39,350
I don't know, sir.

653
00:42:39,351 --> 00:42:41,644
- Keep trying.
- Yes, sir.

654
00:42:41,645 --> 00:42:45,064
- Damage control.
- It's dead, sir.

655
00:42:45,065 --> 00:42:48,109
<i>This is USS Indianapolis.
Does anybody copy?</i>

656
00:42:48,110 --> 00:42:51,112
<i>This is USS Indianapolis trying
to establish any contact.</i>

657
00:42:51,113 --> 00:42:53,614
<i>Indianapolis, Indianapolis,
do you copy?</i>

658
00:42:53,615 --> 00:42:55,116
This is Leyte.

659
00:42:55,117 --> 00:42:56,951
- What's going on?
- Three calls, sir.

660
00:42:56,952 --> 00:42:58,578
One caller identified
himself as the captain.

661
00:42:58,579 --> 00:43:00,413
- I dispatched three tugboats...
- On whose command?

662
00:43:00,414 --> 00:43:02,373
Pull them back!

663
00:43:02,374 --> 00:43:04,542
We don't send anyone out until we
get confirmation of their position.

664
00:43:04,543 --> 00:43:07,128
That could be an enemy sub
trying to draw us out.

665
00:43:07,129 --> 00:43:08,379
- Is that understood?
- Yes, sir.

666
00:43:08,380 --> 00:43:10,980
<i><font color="#D900D9">(MEN SHOUTING,
ALARM BLARING)</font></i>

667
00:43:23,061 --> 00:43:25,146
We're not going to be able
to fight this one off.

668
00:43:25,147 --> 00:43:27,023
She's going down.

669
00:43:27,024 --> 00:43:30,234
Pass the word!
Abandon ship.

670
00:43:30,235 --> 00:43:33,295
Abandon ship!
Abandon ship!

671
00:43:49,588 --> 00:43:52,298
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN</font> :
Help me, father.</i>

672
00:43:52,299 --> 00:43:54,634
Help me, father.

673
00:43:54,635 --> 00:43:56,344
I hear you.

674
00:43:56,345 --> 00:44:00,155
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTS)</font> Help me, father!
I'm scared.

675
00:44:01,642 --> 00:44:04,101
Abandon ship, abandon ship!

676
00:44:04,102 --> 00:44:06,354
Captain's orders, abandon ship!

677
00:44:06,355 --> 00:44:08,535
- Grab the documents, now!
- Aye aye, sir.

678
00:44:15,989 --> 00:44:18,049
All hands on deck!
Abandon ship!

679
00:44:21,537 --> 00:44:24,580
<i><font color="#D900D9">(MEN SHOUTING)</font></i>

680
00:44:24,581 --> 00:44:27,041
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on!

681
00:44:27,042 --> 00:44:28,251
I've got the keys!

