<font color="#D900D9">(WAILING)</font>

1148
01:22:03,382 --> 01:22:05,362
Hey, we got company.

1149
01:22:11,849 --> 01:22:13,619
West.

1150
01:22:22,734 --> 01:22:24,034
<i>WEST:
They're all dead.</i>

1151
01:22:24,035 --> 01:22:25,903
<i>Standish. Cavanaugh.</i>

1152
01:22:25,904 --> 01:22:27,634
Sharks everywhere.

1153
01:22:28,866 --> 01:22:32,660
West, you're okay.

1154
01:22:32,661 --> 01:22:35,371
Forgive me, chap.

1155
01:22:35,372 --> 01:22:37,832
- <font color="#D900D9">(CRYING)</font> I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

1156
01:22:37,833 --> 01:22:39,542
- You're safe.
- I'm so sorry.

1157
01:22:39,543 --> 01:22:40,813
You're safe.

1158
01:22:45,048 --> 01:22:46,478
No!

1159
01:22:53,015 --> 01:22:55,349
Get out of the water!

1160
01:22:55,350 --> 01:22:57,351
Swim! Swim!

1161
01:22:57,352 --> 01:22:59,687
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL SHOUTING)</font>

1162
01:22:59,688 --> 01:23:01,498
Get out!

1163
01:23:10,407 --> 01:23:12,757
<font color="#D900D9">(SCREAMS)</font>

1164
01:23:16,538 --> 01:23:18,518
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CLAMORING)</font>

1165
01:23:20,417 --> 01:23:22,668
No!

1166
01:23:22,669 --> 01:23:24,859
God damn it!

1167
01:23:35,098 --> 01:23:38,601
<i><font color="#D09090">CHARLIE</font> :
"It is the fourth day,</i>

1168
01:23:38,602 --> 01:23:40,832
<i>and many men
have simply given up.</i>

1169
01:23:45,526 --> 01:23:48,945
<i>I've seen the strongest boys,</i>

1170
01:23:48,946 --> 01:23:51,781
<i>their lives full of promise,</i>

1171
01:23:51,782 --> 01:23:55,642
<i>succumb to our horrible
circumstances.</i>

1172
01:23:57,412 --> 01:24:00,892
<i>Others of us feel as though
we are losing our minds."</i>

1173
01:24:03,126 --> 01:24:05,556
<i><font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMS IN DISTANCE)</font></i>

1174
01:24:25,149 --> 01:24:27,709
<i><font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMS IN DISTANCE)</font></i>

1175
01:24:35,784 --> 01:24:38,764
<i><font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMS IN DISTANCE)</font></i>

1176
01:24:39,746 --> 01:24:42,926
<b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b>

1177
01:26:29,773 --> 01:26:31,983
<font color="#D900D9">(HARMONICA MUSIC PLAYING)</font>

1178
01:26:31,984 --> 01:26:35,069
Garrison.

1179
01:26:35,070 --> 01:26:37,210
Garrison, is that...
is that a hallucination?

1180
01:26:39,867 --> 01:26:41,993
That son of a bitch is close.
Can you see it?

1181
01:26:41,994 --> 01:26:44,287
Do you see that?

1182
01:26:44,288 --> 01:26:48,207
Help!
Over here! Over here!

1183
01:26:48,208 --> 01:26:51,002
I can't see.
I ca... I can't see.

1184
01:26:51,003 --> 01:26:53,563
I can't see any...
I can't see anything.

1185
01:26:55,591 --> 01:26:57,008
Wave right here.
He's close.

1186
01:26:57,009 --> 01:26:59,989
- Hey!
- Hey! Hey!

1187
01:27:02,181 --> 01:27:04,599
I'm getting nothing
but static, sir.

1188
01:27:04,600 --> 01:27:06,809
It's that antenna.
I thought you had it looked at.

1189
01:27:06,810 --> 01:27:08,040
I did.

1190
01:27:13,942 --> 01:27:15,752
God damn it.

1191
01:27:18,947 --> 01:27:20,797
Look down!

1192
01:27:28,248 --> 01:27:29,916
We're above something.

1193
01:27:29,917 --> 01:27:31,876
I think it's an oil spill
from a Japanese sub.

1194
01:27:31,877 --> 01:27:34,267
<i>Let's circle back.
Get ready to drop.</i>

1195
01:27:43,055 --> 01:27:46,015
He saw us!
He saw us!

1196
01:27:46,016 --> 01:27:48,059
He saw us!

1197
01:27:48,060 --> 01:27:50,353
Drop below 50!
Hang on!

1198
01:27:50,354 --> 01:27:53,064
Are you sure it was
a Japanese submarine, sir?

1199
01:27:53,065 --> 01:27:56,192
Who else would be out here?
You got eyes on this?

1200
01:27:56,193 --> 01:27:57,383
On my go!

1201
01:28:03,075 --> 01:28:06,953
Are you...
seeing this, skipper?

1202
01:28:06,954 --> 01:28:10,748
You seeing...
seeing this?

1203
01:28:10,749 --> 01:28:12,139
It doesn't see us.

1204
01:28:14,253 --> 01:28:16,653
Sees the oil.

1205
01:28:20,384 --> 01:28:24,303
<i>And drop in three, two, one.</i>

1206
01:28:24,304 --> 01:28:26,074
Wait! Wait!!

1207
01:28:28,809 --> 01:28:31,853
<i>There's got to be 100 men out
there spread out over miles.</i>

1208
01:28:31,854 --> 01:28:33,164
<i>Get on the radio now!</i>

1209
01:28:37,693 --> 01:28:40,111
<i>Hey, look, this is Gambler 17.</i>

1210
01:28:40,112 --> 01:28:42,196
We are flying over hundreds
of boys in the water.

1211
01:28:42,197 --> 01:28:45,837
I repeat, we are flying
over hundreds of boys in the water.

1212
01:28:50,122 --> 01:28:52,081
<i>MAN ON RADIO:
Amber 17, copy this.</i>

1213
01:28:52,082 --> 01:28:53,916
<i>We have to follow protocol.</i>

1214
01:28:53,917 --> 01:28:55,847
<i>The Japanese could be out there.</i>

1215
01:29:00,215 --> 01:29:03,968
Lieutenant! Lieutenant!
Sir, Lieutenant!

1216
01:29:03,969 --> 01:29:05,359
Lieutenant, sir!

1217
01:29:07,764 --> 01:29:09,265
We just got a call in.

1218
01:29:09,266 --> 01:29:11,225
There's something in the water.

1219
01:29:11,226 --> 01:29:15,104
Could be the plane
we're looking for, sir.

1220
01:29:15,105 --> 01:29:18,941
Find all the water we have,
food, too, medical supplies.

1221
01:29:18,942 --> 01:29:21,002
God knows how long
they've been down there.

1222
01:29:39,129 --> 01:29:43,216
Do you see what I see?
There are men everywhere!

1223
01:29:43,217 --> 01:29:44,759
The Japs must have sunk a ship.

1224
01:29:44,760 --> 01:29:46,260
Japs might still be out there

1225
01:29:46,261 --> 01:29:48,741
waiting to sink any ship
that comes along!

1226
01:29:50,808 --> 01:29:53,100
Those boys need help now.

1227
01:29:53,101 --> 01:29:56,437
Sir, request position
permission for a no-no.

1228
01:29:56,438 --> 01:29:58,022
<i>MAN ON RADIO:
Negative!</i>

1229
01:29:58,023 --> 01:30:00,483
<i>Do not land that plane
on open ocean!</i>

1230
01:30:00,484 --> 01:30:02,504
You can't risk
that kind of damage.

1231
01:30:04,446 --> 01:30:06,280
I'm gonna land this plane.

1232
01:30:06,281 --> 01:30:08,331
Land the damn plane, Lieutenant.

1233
01:30:08,332 --> 01:30:09,925
Hang on!

1234
01:30:21,797 --> 01:30:25,133
Holy shit, these guys
are doing a water landing.

1235
01:30:25,134 --> 01:30:28,094
Were almost out of fuel, sir.
We have to go.

1236
01:30:28,095 --> 01:30:29,945
<i>10-4,
heading back to base.</i>

1237
01:30:32,182 --> 01:30:37,353
He saw us!
He saw us! <font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

1238
01:30:37,354 --> 01:30:40,481
<i><font color="#D900D9">(CHEERING)</font></i>

1239
01:30:40,482 --> 01:30:43,276
<b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b>

1240
01:30:43,277 --> 01:30:45,837
<font color="#D900D9">(SHUDDERING)</font>

1241
01:30:49,449 --> 01:30:51,259
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

1242
01:32:26,463 --> 01:32:28,273
<i>Taking on water!</i>

1243
01:32:31,135 --> 01:32:32,435
Holy shit.

1244
01:32:38,267 --> 01:32:40,643
- Pick up the single swimmers.
- Lieutenant,

1245
01:32:40,644 --> 01:32:42,154
wouldn't it be faster
to pick up the ones in groups?

1246
01:32:42,155 --> 01:32:43,980
It'd be a hell of a lot faster,

1247
01:32:43,981 --> 01:32:45,982
but they stand a better chance
of survival in big groups.

1248
01:32:45,983 --> 01:32:48,985
Hey, son, what's your name?
What happened here?

1249
01:32:48,986 --> 01:32:51,320
<font color="#D900D9">(WEAKLY)</font>
Brian Smithwick.

1250
01:32:51,321 --> 01:32:56,591
<i>Signalman first class aboard
the USS Indianapolis.</i>

1251
01:32:58,245 --> 01:32:59,537
<i>Even out!
Straight!</i>

1252
01:32:59,538 --> 01:33:01,289
Lieutenant,
the cabin's getting full.

1253
01:33:01,290 --> 01:33:02,999
Get some more on the wing.
Don't forget this tail.

1254
01:33:03,000 --> 01:33:05,585
We can put some on there.
Watch that cleat!

1255
01:33:05,586 --> 01:33:07,003
<font color="#D900D9">(SOBBING)</font>
We're going home!

1256
01:33:07,004 --> 01:33:08,254
Are you serious...

1257
01:33:08,255 --> 01:33:11,090
<font color="#D900D9">(BABBLING)</font>

1258
01:33:11,091 --> 01:33:13,426
Hey, wait, wait!

1259
01:33:13,427 --> 01:33:15,052
It's our skipper.

1260
01:33:15,053 --> 01:33:17,073
Thank you...

1261
01:33:19,266 --> 01:33:22,018
for... landing!

1262
01:33:22,019 --> 01:33:23,659
We got room for a few more.

1263
01:33:26,064 --> 01:33:28,483
I'm okay!

1264
01:33:28,484 --> 01:33:30,943
Get my men...

1265
01:33:30,944 --> 01:33:32,464
out of the water!

1266
01:33:45,584 --> 01:33:47,710
<i>MAN ON RADIO:
It's the USS Indianapolis.</i>

1267
01:33:47,711 --> 01:33:49,962
That can't be.

1268
01:33:49,963 --> 01:33:51,047
It shouldn't be, but it is.

1269
01:33:51,048 --> 01:33:52,673
This is a class-A
clusterfuck.

1270
01:33:52,674 --> 01:33:54,717
<i>Somebody is gonna pay for this.</i>

1271
01:33:54,718 --> 01:33:57,220
If I were you,
I'd send every ship you got

1272
01:33:57,221 --> 01:33:59,305
before the sharks
get at the rest of them.

1273
01:33:59,306 --> 01:34:01,307
<i>I don't know how many more
I fit on this plane.</i>

1274
01:34:01,308 --> 01:34:02,391
You're putting them
on the plane?

1275
01:34:02,392 --> 01:34:04,352
You'll never get off the water!

1276
01:34:04,353 --> 01:34:07,021
You kidding me?
The plane's shot, Hoss. It's shot to shit.

1277
01:34:07,022 --> 01:34:09,273
We're taking on water.
We're lucky to be afloat.

1278
01:34:09,274 --> 01:34:11,744
You don't want to consider
sending a ship for these boys,

1279
01:34:11,745 --> 01:34:14,085
<i>send one for me.</i>

1280
01:34:17,574 --> 01:34:21,118
<i><font color="#D09090">CHARLIE</font> : "I don't understand
why it took so long.</i>

1281
01:34:21,119 --> 01:34:24,330
<i>At last relief came.</i>

1282
01:34:24,331 --> 01:34:26,582
<i>There wasn't enough room
on the plane</i>

1283
01:34:26,583 --> 01:34:31,587
<i>for all the survivors,
but soon the ships followed,</i>

1284
01:34:31,588 --> 01:34:35,007
<i>the Bassett,
the Ringness, the Talbot,</i>

1285
01:34:35,008 --> 01:34:37,468
<i>the Register, the Dulfilho,</i>

1286
01:34:37,469 --> 01:34:39,359
<i>and the Cecil J. Doyle."</i>

1287
01:34:52,442 --> 01:34:55,611
That's exactly what I want.

1288
01:34:55,612 --> 01:34:58,281
Our hero ship that delivered
the bomb in record time

1289
01:34:58,282 --> 01:35:00,741
got sunk four days ago.

1290
01:35:00,742 --> 01:35:02,802
What?
How many survived?

1291
01:35:04,746 --> 01:35:06,706
317.

1292
01:35:06,707 --> 01:35:10,585
879 men lost their lives.

1293
01:35:10,586 --> 01:35:12,628
Command screwed the pooch
on three SOS calls

1294
01:35:12,629 --> 01:35:14,213
<i>from the Indianapolis.</i>

1295
01:35:14,214 --> 01:35:16,090
That's not including
an intercepted message

1296
01:35:16,091 --> 01:35:19,093
from the Japanese I-58
that did that sinking.

1297
01:35:19,094 --> 01:35:20,595
Son of a bitch.

1298
01:35:20,596 --> 01:35:22,722
The Japanese
on the verge of surrender,

1299
01:35:22,723 --> 01:35:25,516
<i>and that's due in part
to the Indianapolis.</i>

1300
01:35:25,517 --> 01:35:28,561
I don't want to hear about
the sinking in the press

1301
01:35:28,562 --> 01:35:30,188
till I'm damn good and ready.

1302
01:35:30,189 --> 01:35:32,732
Jap surrender
we'll just mention in a news dump.

1303
01:35:32,733 --> 01:35:34,652
Bury it below
some positive news.

1304
01:35:34,653 --> 01:35:36,569
There will still be
an investigation.

1305
01:35:36,570 --> 01:35:37,820
Too many lives were lost.

1306
01:35:37,821 --> 01:35:39,363
With the Pearl Harbor
inquiry going on,

1307
01:35:39,364 --> 01:35:41,407
now ain't the time
to be raising questions

1308
01:35:41,408 --> 01:35:43,576
about military incompetence.

1309
01:35:43,577 --> 01:35:46,287
Or you just suggest
we indict the Big Blue Dick.

1310
01:35:46,288 --> 01:35:50,416
No, I'm saying the press
and the public

1311
01:35:50,417 --> 01:35:53,267
will want somebody's
head on a platter.

1312
01:35:59,176 --> 01:36:01,594
Then we'll give 'em someone.

1313
01:36:01,595 --> 01:36:05,181
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN</font> :
I want to go home!</i>

1314
01:36:05,182 --> 01:36:07,282
<i>I just want to go home!</i>

1315
01:36:10,687 --> 01:36:14,440
<i>Where's the doctor?!
I need a doctor!</i>

1316
01:36:14,441 --> 01:36:16,275
<i><font color="#D09090">WOMAN</font> :
Just lie back, sir.</i>

1317
01:36:16,276 --> 01:36:19,570
- Signalman.
- Yes, sir.

1318
01:36:19,571 --> 01:36:23,301
Did your friend make it?
The boy you jumped over with?

1319
01:36:43,887 --> 01:36:47,390
<i><font color="#D09090">CHARLIE</font> : "Through some terrible
twist of fate,</i>

1320
01:36:47,391 --> 01:36:50,726
<i>it turns out that I am
one of the only officers</i>

1321
01:36:50,727 --> 01:36:52,812
<i>that survived.</i>

1322
01:36:52,813 --> 01:36:56,399
<i>Many of those that died
were our dear friends.</i>

1323
01:36:56,400 --> 01:36:58,484
<i>It will be a tremendous
burden for you</i>

1324
01:36:58,485 --> 01:37:00,611
<i>to have to tell their wives</i>

1325
01:37:00,612 --> 01:37:02,738
<i>that all their husbands perished</i>

1326
01:37:02,739 --> 01:37:07,549
<i>while yours,
the Captain, lived."</i>

1327
01:37:09,621 --> 01:37:11,539
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN</font> :
Anybody seen Cavanaugh?</i>

1328
01:37:11,540 --> 01:37:15,418
<i>Did Cavanaugh make it?</i>

1329
01:37:15,419 --> 01:37:16,878
<i>What about Standish?</i>

1330
01:37:16,879 --> 01:37:19,519
Garrison,
9:00. 9:00.

1331
01:37:23,594 --> 01:37:24,864
Stick your hand out.

1332
01:37:27,431 --> 01:37:30,224
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>
It's Theodore, you dummy.

1333
01:37:30,225 --> 01:37:32,768
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHTER)</font>

1334
01:37:32,769 --> 01:37:35,396
You little turd!
<font color="#D900D9">(LAUGHS)</font>

1335
01:37:35,397 --> 01:37:38,441
We found your book
on a dead guy, man.

1336
01:37:38,442 --> 01:37:40,401
I gave it to a sailor
for comfort.

1337
01:37:40,402 --> 01:37:43,321
I ain't ready to go down
God's toilet bowl yet.

1338
01:37:43,322 --> 01:37:45,302
<i>I missed you guys!</i>

1339
01:37:54,249 --> 01:37:55,958
I found that...

1340
01:37:55,959 --> 01:37:58,586
in the gutter...

1341
01:37:58,587 --> 01:38:00,797
two weeks ago.

1342
01:38:00,798 --> 01:38:02,648
You believe that?

1343
01:38:04,426 --> 01:38:06,260
Thanks.

1344
01:38:06,261 --> 01:38:09,764
Don't... don't thank me.
I was going to come here.

1345
01:38:09,765 --> 01:38:14,310
I was going to tell you that
I didn't know whose it was.

1346
01:38:14,311 --> 01:38:16,687
But I knew.

1347
01:38:16,688 --> 01:38:19,816
I knew it was D'Antonio's.

1348
01:38:19,817 --> 01:38:22,917
I was gonna pawn it
to pay some debt.

1349
01:38:26,323 --> 01:38:31,953
I'm not just like some
everyday normal kind of asshole, Bama.

1350
01:38:31,954 --> 01:38:33,764
I'm a special kind.

1351
01:38:36,667 --> 01:38:39,001
I'm sorry.

1352
01:38:39,002 --> 01:38:41,402
I'm so sorry.

1353
01:38:44,550 --> 01:38:46,610
<i><font color="#D900D9">(CROWD CHEERING)</font></i>

1354
01:38:53,517 --> 01:38:55,393
<i>MALE REPORTER:
The war is over.</i>

1355
01:38:55,394 --> 01:38:58,729
<i>Atomic bombs have been dropped
on Hiroshima and Nagasaki,</i>

1356
01:38:58,730 --> 01:39:02,024
<i>and Japan has surrendered
to the Allied powers.</i>

1357
01:39:02,025 --> 01:39:04,485
<i><font color="#D09090">CHARLIE</font> :
"The packages we delivered</i>

1358
01:39:04,486 --> 01:39:07,363
<i>worked
with devastating accuracy.</i>

1359
01:39:07,364 --> 01:39:09,824
<i>The men of the USS Indianapolis
returned home..."</i>

1360
01:39:09,825 --> 01:39:12,285
<i>MALE REPORTER:
A joyous day indeed.</i>

1361
01:39:12,286 --> 01:39:14,036
<i>Tickertape parades
are the order of the day</i>

1362
01:39:14,037 --> 01:39:16,414
<i>for all our brave American GIs,</i>

1363
01:39:16,415 --> 01:39:18,374
<i>both those who came back</i>

1364
01:39:18,375 --> 01:39:20,543
<i>and those courageous boys
who have given their lives.</i>

1365
01:39:20,544 --> 01:39:22,734
<i><font color="#D09090">CHARLIE</font> : "Not all of them
with good news."</i>

1366
01:39:31,305 --> 01:39:34,682
<i>"For them,
the war was over."</i>

1367
01:39:34,683 --> 01:39:36,767
Mom!

1368
01:39:36,768 --> 01:39:38,561
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

1369
01:39:38,562 --> 01:39:41,712
<b><font color="#FFFF00">[♪♪]</font></b>

1370
01:39:47,070 --> 01:39:50,406
<i>"But for me, the battle
was just beginning."</i>

1371
01:39:50,407 --> 01:39:51,532
I'm here.

1372
01:39:51,533 --> 01:39:53,534
<i><font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLES)</font></i>

1373
01:39:53,535 --> 01:39:56,005
<font color="#D900D9">(TELEPHONE RINGS)</font>

1374
01:40:07,633 --> 01:40:10,426
<i>McWHORTER:
My boy. My baby boy.</i>

1375
01:40:10,427 --> 01:40:12,527
I'll never get to see him!

1376
01:40:14,389 --> 01:40:16,159
<font color="#D900D9">(GRUNTING)</font>

1377
01:40:20,687 --> 01:40:22,037
<i><font color="#D900D9">(MAN SCREAMING)</font></i>

1378
01:40:26,485 --> 01:40:28,375
<i><font color="#D900D9">(THUNDER RUMBLES,
TELEPHONE RINGS)</font></i>

1379
01:40:35,661 --> 01:40:37,578
McVay residence.

1380
01:40:37,579 --> 01:40:40,456
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN</font> : I hope you burn in hell
for what you did.</i>

1381
01:40:40,457 --> 01:40:42,677
Just hang up, Charlie.

1382
01:40:44,461 --> 01:40:45,941
<i>Burn in hell!</i>

1383
01:40:48,799 --> 01:40:51,467
We need you back, Charlie.

1384
01:40:51,468 --> 01:40:55,721
Me, your boy...

1385
01:40:55,722 --> 01:40:57,807
we need you.

1386
01:40:57,808 --> 01:41:00,476
A lot of boys needed me.

1387
01:41:00,477 --> 01:41:02,747
You did all you could.

1388
01:41:12,739 --> 01:41:14,829
<i><font color="#D09090">CLARA</font> :
I hear you got your promotion.</i>

1389
01:41:14,830 --> 01:41:17,410
I turned it down.

1390
01:41:17,411 --> 01:41:20,163
I'm moving to Washington, DC,
going to law school.

1391
01:41:20,164 --> 01:41:22,670
Might even help my uncle
on his next campaign.

1392
01:41:22,671 --> 01:41:25,835
Well, I wish you
all the luck in the world, Brian.

1393
01:41:25,836 --> 01:41:27,670
You deserve it.

1394
01:41:27,671 --> 01:41:32,425
Clara, I, um...

1395
01:41:32,426 --> 01:41:34,927
I've been through
just about the scariest thing

1396
01:41:34,928 --> 01:41:37,763
that a man could face
out there on the ocean.

1397
01:41:37,764 --> 01:41:39,599
I don't know that
that's something

1398
01:41:39,600 --> 01:41:41,517
I'm ever going to get over.

1399
01:41:41,518 --> 01:41:42,852
You see, I've been afraid

1400
01:41:42,853 --> 01:41:44,145
to live my life to the fullest.

1401
01:41:44,146 --> 01:41:47,064
I've been afraid a long time.

1402
01:41:47,065 --> 01:41:49,942
<i>- <font color="#D900D9">(DOOR OPENS, FOOTSTEPS)</font>
- Afraid of what?</i>

1403
01:41:49,943 --> 01:41:51,861
<i><font color="#D900D9">(MAN SPEAKING ON RADIO)</font></i>

1404
01:41:51,862 --> 01:41:56,382
Just, well,
not being good enough.

1405
01:41:57,034 --> 01:41:59,076
Yeah.

1406
01:41:59,077 --> 01:42:02,038
About being rejected.

1407
01:42:02,039 --> 01:42:05,833
Rejected?
By who?

1408
01:42:05,834 --> 01:42:09,003
By you, Clara.

1409
01:42:09,004 --> 01:42:14,074
I have been in love with you
since the day that we met.

1410
01:42:16,553 --> 01:42:18,054
And I, um...

1411
01:42:18,055 --> 01:42:21,057
<font color="#D900D9">(GASPS)</font>

1412
01:42:21,058 --> 01:42:23,017
Marriage?

1413
01:42:23,018 --> 01:42:25,728
Brian...

1414
01:42:25,729 --> 01:42:27,063
Mike and I are having...

1415
01:42:27,064 --> 01:42:30,107
A baby, yeah, I know.

1416
01:42:30,108 --> 01:42:33,152
But you see,
Mike was like a brother to me,

1417
01:42:33,153 --> 01:42:36,239
and that baby
is going to need a father.

1418
01:42:36,240 --> 01:42:38,658
<i>And so I would be honored</i>

1419
01:42:38,659 --> 01:42:41,549
if you would at least
consider being my wife.

1420
01:42:44,206 --> 01:42:48,543
You don't gotta love me back
or anything like that.

1421
01:42:48,544 --> 01:42:52,088
And we might never
be as rich as your folks.

1422
01:42:52,089 --> 01:42:56,259
But we could start
a fresh life in DC.

1423
01:42:56,260 --> 01:42:58,511
I know you already got one ring,

1424
01:42:58,512 --> 01:43:00,332
but I thought maybe
two was better than one.

1425
01:43:05,102 --> 01:43:08,062
After all he's been through,
they're putting him on trial.

1426
01:43:08,063 --> 01:43:10,148
Sounds like they're
looking for a scapegoat.

1427
01:43:10,149 --> 01:43:13,776
Louise, it...
it's complicated.

1428
01:43:13,777 --> 01:43:16,237
What's complicated?
Admiral.

1429
01:43:16,238 --> 01:43:17,613
Captain.

1430
01:43:17,614 --> 01:43:19,198
Would you gentlemen
like some tea?

1431
01:43:19,199 --> 01:43:22,201
Thank you, Louise.

1432
01:43:22,202 --> 01:43:23,622
<i>REPORTER ON RADIO:
Bumped into the submarine,</i>

1433
01:43:23,623 --> 01:43:25,246
<i>which had fired the torpedoes.</i>

1434
01:43:25,247 --> 01:43:27,290
<i>Members of the
tanker's crew related...</i>

1435
01:43:27,291 --> 01:43:29,041
<font color="#D900D9">(SIGHS)</font>

1436
01:43:29,042 --> 01:43:31,130
<i>The President
withheld immediate comment...</i>

1437
01:43:31,131 --> 01:43:33,921
<i><font color="#D09090">ADMIRAL</font> : Charlie, as far as
they were concerned,</i>

1438
01:43:33,922 --> 01:43:35,301
<i>you were on a secret mission</i>

1439
01:43:35,302 --> 01:43:36,883
<i>under the command
of the President.</i>

1440
01:43:36,884 --> 01:43:38,801
<i><font color="#D900D9">(RADIO SWITCHES OFF)</font></i>

1441
01:43:38,802 --> 01:43:43,639
<i>And since their orders were
to never announce arrivals,</i>

1442
01:43:43,640 --> 01:43:45,057
<i>they'll argue that they</i>

1443
01:43:45,058 --> 01:43:48,578
were not supposed to announce
non-arrivals either.

1444
01:43:50,606 --> 01:43:52,190
So what now?

1445
01:43:52,191 --> 01:43:54,711
I found outside counsel.

1446
01:44:04,995 --> 01:44:06,345
What I'm about to tell you...

1447
01:44:09,041 --> 01:44:10,931
can't ever leave this room.

1448
01:44:17,341 --> 01:44:21,761
Four days before your ship
was sunk by the Japanese...

1449
01:44:21,762 --> 01:44:26,098
there was another US ship
in those same waters.

1450
01:44:26,099 --> 01:44:27,619
<i>The USS Underhill.</i>

1451
01:44:30,687 --> 01:44:34,627
She was torpedoed...
and sunk.

1452
01:44:37,319 --> 01:44:41,989
Point being, you should
have had an escort.

1453
01:44:41,990 --> 01:44:45,618
You should have had sonar.

1454
01:44:45,619 --> 01:44:47,799
Charlie, I am so sorry.

1455
01:44:51,333 --> 01:44:53,353
The trial will be in Washington.

1456
01:44:59,258 --> 01:45:03,136
<font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEER)</font>

1457
01:45:03,137 --> 01:45:04,637
This one right here, fellas,

1458
01:45:04,638 --> 01:45:06,848
is to being back
on solid ground.

1459
01:45:06,849 --> 01:45:10,017
- <font color="#D900D9">(ALL CHEER)</font>
- To never seeing another shark again.

1460
01:45:10,018 --> 01:45:14,230
To wishing our Captain luck
in this bullshit trial.

1461
01:45:14,231 --> 01:45:17,024
To all the good men
we lost at sea.

1462
01:45:17,025 --> 01:45:19,777
- Amen.
- Amen.

1463
01:45:19,778 --> 01:45:20,778
<i><font color="#D900D9">(UPBEAT JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)</font></i>

1464
01:45:20,779 --> 01:45:22,738
Excuse me, boys.

1465
01:45:22,739 --> 01:45:24,115
See something you like, Alvin?

1466
01:45:24,116 --> 01:45:27,160
Oh, no, yeah, no I...

1467
01:45:27,161 --> 01:45:29,704
I recognize one of those rings.

1468
01:45:29,705 --> 01:45:33,249
But, uh, not the other one.

1469
01:45:33,250 --> 01:45:36,252
I got it from my husband, Bama.

1470
01:45:36,253 --> 01:45:39,113
Your husband.
Oh.

1471
01:45:44,261 --> 01:45:47,680
You got something
you want to say, Alvin?

1472
01:45:47,681 --> 01:45:49,765
Isn't that D'Antonio's girl?

1473
01:45:49,766 --> 01:45:54,270
Yeah, she was. So?

1474
01:45:54,271 --> 01:45:56,105
I mean, a fella married

1475
01:45:56,106 --> 01:45:58,107
his buddy's pregnant girlfriend?

1476
01:45:58,108 --> 01:46:00,151
That's...

1477
01:46:00,152 --> 01:46:02,153
well, he's a better man than me.

1478
01:46:02,154 --> 01:46:05,781
Yeah, I'll drink to that.

1479
01:46:05,782 --> 01:46:08,284
Hey, McVay's trial starts
at 0900.

1480
01:46:08,285 --> 01:46:10,185
Think we ought a be there
about an hour early.

1481
01:46:12,122 --> 01:46:14,874
<font color="#D900D9">(CROWD SHOUTING ANGRILY)</font>

1482
01:46:14,875 --> 01:46:16,292
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN</font> :
Sir! Sir!</i>

1483
01:46:16,293 --> 01:46:18,127
<i>Are you expecting
to be court martialed?</i>

1484
01:46:18,128 --> 01:46:20,880
<i>Sir, answer the question!</i>

1485
01:46:20,881 --> 01:46:22,465
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN 2</font> : Do you feel
personally responsible</i>

1486
01:46:22,466 --> 01:46:24,226
<i>for the loss
of your men? Captain!</i>

1487
01:46:25,803 --> 01:46:28,413
<i><font color="#D900D9">(CROWD CHANTING
"MCVAY MUST PAY" OUTSIDE)</font></i>

1488
01:46:29,973 --> 01:46:32,850
Captain McVay,
you're being accused

1489
01:46:32,851 --> 01:46:35,144
of hazarding your ship
by failing to zigzag

1490
01:46:35,145 --> 01:46:38,314
as an evasive maneuver
and failing to abandon ship

1491
01:46:38,315 --> 01:46:40,817
in a timely manner.

1492
01:46:40,818 --> 01:46:44,237
For the benefit of the court,
how do you plead?

1493
01:46:44,238 --> 01:46:45,404
Not guilty.

1494
01:46:45,405 --> 01:46:47,795
<font color="#D900D9">(AUDIENCE MURMURS)</font>

1495
01:46:49,993 --> 01:46:51,410
And when the ship was hit,

1496
01:46:51,411 --> 01:46:54,247
did you hear any directives
from your Captain?

1497
01:46:54,248 --> 01:46:57,416
I went to the bridge.
Commander Cavanaugh was there.

1498
01:46:57,417 --> 01:46:58,835
He told me that Captain McVay

1499
01:46:58,836 --> 01:47:00,962
had given the order
to abandon ship.

1500
01:47:00,963 --> 01:47:04,006
But you never got the order
from Captain McVay.

1501
01:47:04,007 --> 01:47:06,384
- Not initially, but...
- Thank you, sir, that'll suffice.

1502
01:47:06,385 --> 01:47:08,525
No further questions,
your honor.

1503
01:47:14,893 --> 01:47:17,854
Why didn't you object?
That was military protocol.

1504
01:47:17,855 --> 01:47:22,400
<i><font color="#D900D9">(GAVEL BANGS)</font></i>

1505
01:47:22,401 --> 01:47:25,862
Captain McVay, what, pray tell,

1506
01:47:25,863 --> 01:47:27,280
is your theory on zigzagging?

1507
01:47:27,281 --> 01:47:29,490
Not so effective
against kaitens,

1508
01:47:29,491 --> 01:47:32,539
It's a new Japanese weapon
a manned suicide torpedo,

1509
01:47:32,540 --> 01:47:34,829
<i>like an underwater
kamikaze plane.</i>

1510
01:47:34,830 --> 01:47:36,539
Hard to hit what you can't see.

1511
01:47:36,540 --> 01:47:39,292
And on that night?

1512
01:47:39,293 --> 01:47:41,878
<i><font color="#D09090">CHARLIE</font> : Let's get through this weather
is quickly as possible.</i>

1513
01:47:41,879 --> 01:47:43,546
Cease zigzagging
until the fog clears.

1514
01:47:43,547 --> 01:47:45,047
<i>Full speed ahead.</i>

1515
01:47:45,048 --> 01:47:46,299
Tell us about
the sequence of events

1516
01:47:46,300 --> 01:47:48,342
the night you were struck.

1517
01:47:48,343 --> 01:47:52,430
We'd been hit.
The question was how bad.

1518
01:47:52,431 --> 01:47:55,183
<i>The Indianapolis
is a strong ship.</i>

1519
01:47:55,184 --> 01:47:57,393
She's built
like a floating tank.

1520
01:47:57,394 --> 01:47:59,901
We had survived
multiple attacks before

1521
01:47:59,902 --> 01:48:01,272
<i>so we had to assess the damage.</i>

1522
01:48:01,273 --> 01:48:04,233
- General quarters!
- We had no electrical.

1523
01:48:04,234 --> 01:48:06,903
Did you get the SOS out?

1524
01:48:06,904 --> 01:48:08,488
Pass the word!
Abandon ship.

1525
01:48:08,489 --> 01:48:11,908
So you called abandon ship
about six to eight minutes

1526
01:48:11,909 --> 01:48:14,494
<i>- after you were struck.
- Abandon ship!</i>

1527
01:48:14,495 --> 01:48:16,829
How did you personally
abandon ship?

1528
01:48:16,830 --> 01:48:18,310
Go, go!

1529
01:48:24,421 --> 01:48:26,271
Can anyone hear me?

1530
01:48:31,303 --> 01:48:32,653
Paul?

1531
01:48:34,264 --> 01:48:35,874
Paul.

1532
01:48:40,521 --> 01:48:44,607
<i><font color="#D09090">CHARLIE</font> : It was the last
I saw of my men that night</i>

1533
01:48:44,608 --> 01:48:47,288
<i>and the last I saw of our ship.</i>

1534
01:48:58,288 --> 01:48:59,968
Nothing further, Your Honor.

1535
01:49:12,469 --> 01:49:15,972
We wish to call to the stand
the only submarine commander

1536
01:49:15,973 --> 01:49:19,058
who is relevant to this case
because he was there.

1537
01:49:19,059 --> 01:49:22,228
The United States government
calls Captain Hashimoto

1538
01:49:22,229 --> 01:49:24,605
of the Imperial Japanese Navy.

1539
01:49:24,606 --> 01:49:27,126
<font color="#D900D9">(AUDIENCE MURMURING)</font>

1540
01:49:39,121 --> 01:49:42,311
<i><font color="#D09090">JUDGE</font> : Order in the court.
Order in the court.</i>

1541
01:49:49,381 --> 01:49:52,383
<i><font color="#D09090">PROSECUTOR</font> : Captain Hashimoto,
you understand</i>

1542
01:49:52,384 --> 01:49:54,969
<i>that you are under oath
to tell the truth,</i>

1543
01:49:54,970 --> 01:49:58,473
the whole truth,
and nothing but the truth.

1544
01:49:58,474 --> 01:50:01,601
But you're not Christian,
are you?

1545
01:50:01,602 --> 01:50:03,311
Shintoist.

1546
01:50:03,312 --> 01:50:06,564
We believe that the soul
exists after death,

1547
01:50:06,565 --> 01:50:09,233
and, yes,
I understand the difference

1548
01:50:09,234 --> 01:50:11,360
between truth and falsehood.

1549
01:50:11,361 --> 01:50:14,071
Very well.

1550
01:50:14,072 --> 01:50:17,342
Tell us about your actions
on the night in question.

1551
01:50:25,209 --> 01:50:27,269
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING JAPANESE)</font>

1552
01:50:31,298 --> 01:50:33,318
Did you fire your kaitens?

1553
01:51:18,303 --> 01:51:22,348
<i>So the USS Indianapolis was sunk</i>

1554
01:51:22,349 --> 01:51:24,225
using conventional torpedoes.

1555
01:51:24,226 --> 01:51:26,018
<i>Yes.</i>

1556
01:51:26,019 --> 01:51:29,605
In your opinion,
if the ship had been zigzagging,

1557
01:51:29,606 --> 01:51:31,576
would it have made a difference?

1558
01:51:37,114 --> 01:51:38,489
No.

1559
01:51:38,490 --> 01:51:40,449
<i>We were too close.</i>

1560
01:51:40,450 --> 01:51:42,410
<i>I fired six torpedoes.</i>

1561
01:51:42,411 --> 01:51:44,511
<i>He had no chance to escape.</i>

1562
01:51:55,382 --> 01:51:57,442
No further questions,
Your Honor.

1563
01:52:03,223 --> 01:52:05,766
<font color="#D900D9">(CHANTING)</font> McVay must pay!
McVay must pay!

1564
01:52:05,767 --> 01:52:08,197
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN</font> : Call to order.
Please rise.</i>

1565
01:52:11,440 --> 01:52:14,319
On the first count,
failure to give the order

1566
01:52:14,320 --> 01:52:16,319
<i>to abandon ship
in a timely manner,</i>

1567
01:52:16,320 --> 01:52:17,695
<i>we find the defendant,</i>

1568
01:52:17,696 --> 01:52:21,824
<i>Captain Charles Butler
McVay III, not guilty.</i>

1569
01:52:21,825 --> 01:52:24,135
<i><font color="#D900D9">(GAVEL BANGS,
AUDIENCE WHISPERING)</font></i>

1570
01:52:33,212 --> 01:52:35,562
<i><font color="#D900D9">(AUDIENCE MURMURS)</font></i>

1571
01:52:49,520 --> 01:52:53,314
What does that mean?
What happened?

1572
01:52:53,315 --> 01:52:58,277
They only announce
the not-guilty verdicts.

1573
01:52:58,278 --> 01:53:00,404
He's been found guilty
of hazarding the ship

1574
01:53:00,405 --> 01:53:01,864
by failing to zigzag.

1575
01:53:01,865 --> 01:53:04,492
<i>They court-martial
our captain</i>

1576
01:53:04,493 --> 01:53:06,786
and didn't mention
all of our dead?

1577
01:53:06,787 --> 01:53:09,307
They should be building
him a monument.

1578
01:53:11,583 --> 01:53:14,127
Charlie, I want you to know,

1579
01:53:14,128 --> 01:53:16,148
I'd rather this
played out differently.

1580
01:53:34,565 --> 01:53:37,400
Hundreds of ships
were sunk during the war,

1581
01:53:37,401 --> 01:53:40,278
and yours is the only
court-martial?

1582
01:53:40,279 --> 01:53:41,904
It stinks.

1583
01:53:41,905 --> 01:53:43,505
Thank you.

1584
01:53:45,576 --> 01:53:47,785
<i><font color="#D09090">MAN</font> : Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Who's that guy?</i>

1585
01:53:47,786 --> 01:53:49,846
<i>Who is that guy?</i>

1586
01:53:51,748 --> 01:53:53,666
I need a few minutes alone.

1587
01:53:53,667 --> 01:53:55,585
Captain...
Captain, how do you feel

1588
01:53:55,586 --> 01:53:57,712
<i>about this being the worst
naval disaster in history?</i>

1589
01:53:57,713 --> 01:54:01,233
- Captain...
- Is it true you were denied your choice of an attorney?

1590
01:54:12,186 --> 01:54:14,366
<font color="#D900D9">(SPEAKING JAPANESE)</font>

1591
01:54:20,194 --> 01:54:22,862
This would never happen
in Japan.

1592
01:54:22,863 --> 01:54:25,448
If the roles were reversed,

1593
01:54:25,449 --> 01:54:29,389
you would not be called in
to testify on anyone's behalf.

1594
01:54:30,662 --> 01:54:33,289
Was there anything
I could have done?

1595
01:54:33,290 --> 01:54:36,292
You were exposed.

1596
01:54:36,293 --> 01:54:37,903
We were there.

1597
01:54:41,507 --> 01:54:44,967
As a commander
in the Imperial Japanese Navy,

1598
01:54:44,968 --> 01:54:47,738
it was my duty to kill you.

1599
01:54:52,476 --> 01:54:54,406
But as a man...

1600
01:54:58,732 --> 01:55:00,672
I have regrets.

1601
01:55:03,737 --> 01:55:07,927
I had a good idea
of what we were carrying.

1602
01:55:11,495 --> 01:55:13,055
I, too, did my duty.

1603
01:55:17,668 --> 01:55:20,920
But as a man...

1604
01:55:20,921 --> 01:55:23,339
I find no...

1605
01:55:23,340 --> 01:55:25,860
honor in it.

1606
01:55:29,847 --> 01:55:31,681
I often wonder
how things would be

1607
01:55:31,682 --> 01:55:35,452
if I had stopped you before
you completed your mission.

1608
